title: Interceptor Bindings Survive Save/Restore (ADR-208 AC-9)
story: dungeo
description: The rug push interceptor fires again on restored state — bindings are per-world code wiring, not save data

---

# Get to the Living Room
> north
[OK: contains "North of House"]

> east
[OK: contains "Behind House"]

> open window
[OK: contains "open"]

> west
[OK: contains "Kitchen"]

> west
[OK: contains "Living Room"]

# Checkpoint BEFORE the rug is moved
$save ac9-checkpoint

# Rug push routes through the story's RugPushInterceptor (ADR-118)
> push rug
[OK: contains "trap door"]

# Restore to the pre-push state
$restore ac9-checkpoint

# The rug is back in place and the interceptor must fire again on the
# restored world — bindings live on the world instance, not in the save blob
> push rug
[OK: contains "trap door"]
